{
  "stem": "10588.9",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So I wanted to have the names.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And then my son, our youngest son, Michael, was born.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I'm not going to go into the story.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "But both Michael and I were called a miracle, because I was extremely sick.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I almost died when I gave birth to him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But somehow, we survived, and everybody was amazed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And Michael is a beautiful young man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And I made three nice bar mitzahs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "The fourth bar mitzah, I said, I did for my friends.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Now I wanted to go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "To Israel.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "If I lived from the gate of Auschwitz to go to Israel, 2,000 years, my people prayed next year in Jerusalem, and I was the lucky one, that I can go.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "So I want to go for all of them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Especially, I found out that after the war, everybody was looking for everybody.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "So on my father's side, his sisters survived because they were sent to USSR.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And because of that, they survived.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "They only lost the youngest child, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "But not because he was killed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Because he died of starvation and sickness.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "But the rest survive, and they went to Israel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was when I went the first time I decided to go for my son's bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was in 1978.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In 1978, from 1934, I have not seen my cousin Gitel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my cousin, by the time I came, the only cousin that survived on my father's side was [NON-ENGLISH], because her sister died in Israel, and my aunt died in Israel.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They died the same day, because my cousin [NON-ENGLISH] had-- I forgot how you call this kind of pregnancy, that was outside the tubes.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she didn't understand.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She didn't take care.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So she died.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
